news.title: DB Realty posts Rs 506.40 crore profit in Q4 FY22
news.para: The company's total consolidated income stood at Rs 214.76 crore in Q4 FY22, a growth of 356.74 per cent from Rs 47.02 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: NBCC's net profit dips 52% in Q4 FY22
news.para: The company's total consolidated income stood at Rs 2,496.44 crore in Q4 FY22, a dip of 10.59 per cent from Rs 2,792 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit jumps 37% to over Rs 5 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total income increased to Rs 252.66 crore in the quarter under review from Rs 222.43 crore in the fourth quarter of FY21.

news.title: ASK Property Investment Advisors raises Rs 610 crore fund to invest in realty assets
news.para: "Domestic investors account for 50 per cent of the real estate fund raised, while overseas investors account for the remaining 50 per cent. We are targeting a fund size of Rs 2,000 crore," he added.

news.title: Maharashtra govt's slum authority to expedite declaration of slums for rehabilitation
news.para: There are several slums in Mumbai city and suburban area existing on private lands as well as lands owned by public authorities and this policy decision will be applicable to all of these slums.

news.title: Omaxe posts Rs 36.62 crore net loss in Jan-March quarter
news.para: Total income fell to Rs 172.86 crore in the fourth quarter of the last fiscal from Rs 191.87 crore a year ago. Omaxe posted a net loss of Rs 161.61 crore in the last fiscal against a net loss of Rs 235.21 crore in 2020-21.

news.title: TDI Infratech to invest Rs 600-crore in Punjab in next three years
news.para: To be developed in an area of approximately 1.3 lakh square feet, Parkstreet will be a high-street concept with pre-lease showrooms, food court, multiplex, rooftop bar and all other world-class amenities that appeal to the young, aspirational buyers in the region.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of MPS group firms, four others to recover investors' money
news.para: The 20 properties put on the block, which include land parcels, storied buildings, an office space, a commercial space and a flat, are situated across West Bengal, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in a notice.

news.title: Ashiana Housing's sales bookings rise 7% to Rs 573.25 crore in FY22
news.para: "Sales price improved to Rs 3,883 per square feet in FY22 from Rs 3,571 per square feet in the FY21, driven by increasing prices across projects and changing mix towards higher-priced projects," the company said.

news.title: FIRs to be filed against 99 real estate developers in Jalandhar
news.para: DC Ghanshyam Thori has asked police to register FIRs against 99 real-estate developers under Punjab Apartment and Property Regulation Act (Papra) for developing illegal colonies in the district over the last two years.

news.title: Telangana government to e-auction plots at Turkayamjal
news.para: Any individual or group of individuals are free to bid for these plots which can be used for the construction of apartments, houses, or commercial complexes.

news.title: Indore civic body yet to achieve 75% target of rainwater harvesting system installation
news.para: IMC Commissioner Pratibha Pal, during a review meeting, on Saturday instructed the officials concerned to geotag all such structures with a rainwater harvesting system installed at its roof.

news.title: Nashik civic body installs rainwater harvest systems in its 70 properties
news.para: ​The civic body’s city engineer Shivkumar Vanjari said the NMC has been taking initiatives to install rainwater harvesting systems at all its buildings in a bid to increase the groundwater level since last year.

news.title: Smart City projects in Mangaluru will be completed by December: Minister
news.para: Various Smart City projects including the new indoor stadium near Urwa Market, development of Mangala Stadium, pedestrian plaza near Clock Tower, International Swimming Pool at Yemmekere, Kadri Park development and smart roads are being expedited, the minister said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body gives more time to apply for plots
news.para: Factors such as the somewhat higher prices for the Vizag layouts and the undeveloped plots (the VMRDA will complete these layouts within 12 months from the date of agreement with allottees) might have led to the lukewarm response.
